Instructions detail Unix system administration for web servers (NGINX/Apache, MySQL/MariaDB) and YAccess installation, including network setup and file permissions.

Flush Priveledges(centos)


/etc/init.d/mysqld stop

mysqld_safe --skip-grant-tables &

mysql -uroot

use mysql;

update user set password=PASSWORD("f!lAsia888") where User='root';



flush privileges;

quit

/etc/init.d/mysqld stop
 /etc/init.d/mysqld start


-----IP is allowed to flush ----

mysql -u root -p

use mysql

GRANT ALL ON *.* to root@'192.168.60.1' IDENTIFIED BY 'f!lAsia888';

FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
